<div id="homeCenterTopBgPurple">

<div id="homeCenterTopText">
<span class="formColPurp">What is Genital Herpes?</span><br /> 
Genital herpes is a sexually transmitted infection that's caused by the herpes simplex virus (HSV), and is transmitted through unprotected and oral sex. Anyone who is sexually active can catch genital herpes and if the genital herpes is left untreated it may spread to other parts of the body.

<p><span class="formColPurp">How can I get genital herpes?</span><br /> 
It is caught when the virus enters through small cracks in the skin or the soft lining of the mouth, vagina, rectum or urethra. It may then stay inactive during which time you are not infectious, or cause an outbreak of sores.</p>
 
<p><span class="formColPurp">What are the symptoms?</span><br /> 
The most common reported symptom is weeping blisters in the genital area, buttocks or the tops of the thighs but sufferers can also experience flu-like symptoms, irritation in the genital area or pain when urinating.</p>

<p><span class="formColPurp">What treatments are available?</span><br /> 
While there is no cure for genital herpes, Aciclovir antiviral tablets shortens the duration and severity of a herpes outbreak.</p>  

<p><span class="formColPurp">How do I order genital herpes medication?</span><br /> 
There are three simples steps involved. After registering and answering a short health questionnaire, a UK GMC registered doctor will review your answers and advise you on the appropriate treatment. After which the medication will be sent to you for next day delivery. If the medication is not safe for you to take, or is not in your best interest, an alternative treatment plan will be suggested, and you will be provided with a full, no quibble refund.</p>

<p><span class="formColPurp">Who should not use the genital herpes treatment service?</span><br /> 
You should not use this service if you are allergic to aciclovir or have liver or kidney disease, or if you are pregnant or breastfeeding.</p>


<p class="formColPurp"><a href="https://www.conveniencemedical.com/genital-herpes-apply2.php" class="PurpleLink">Order one course of Aciclovir treatment: &pound;25.99</a></strong></p>

